  "summaries": [
    {
      "id": 821913,
      "category": "team",
      "content": "Reflected XSS was found in the AI Playground OAuth handler (CVE-2026-1721) due to unescaped interpolation of the error_description parameter into a <script> tag by the researcher.\nA targeted attacker could execute JavaScript to access session-based chat history or interact with connected MCP servers on the victim's behalf during the user's session following a user interaction to click a phishing link.\nThis issue is patched now and users of the open-source Agents SDK should upgrade to v0.3.10\n\nDisclosed responsibly by Nishant Kumawat via Cloudflare Bug Bounty program on Hackerone",
